author: COMSOL
description: This example demonstrates the stress analysis of an elastic chain sprocket assembly. The system consists of a roller chain wrapped around two sprockets in 3D. All the components of the systems are assumed as elastic bodies. An angular velocity is prescribed on the driver sprocket and load torque is applied on the driven sprocket. A transient analysis is performed to understand the load path, contact forces, the stress distribution in various components of the chain drive.
